<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
This species was first recorded from Venezuela by 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A" journalOrPublisher="Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales, Entomologia" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="57 - 236" title="El genero Berosus (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae) en America del Sur." volume="6" year="1989">Oliva (1989)</bibRefCitation>
from Santa Barbara in Barinas State, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="183 - 230" title="Some types of Berosus (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae) kept in the collections of the Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique." volume="129" year="1993">Oliva (1993)</bibRefCitation>
later omitted Venezuela because of some doubt about the identity of the Venezuelan specimens; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen, M" journalOrPublisher="Hydrophiloidea (s. str.) (Coleoptera). Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" title="World Catalogue of Insects. Volume 2." year="1999">Hansen (1999)</bibRefCitation>
based the distribution data of this species on the latter paper. The first author examined again the specimens from Barinas and confirmed they have all the characters of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Berosus festivus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festivus">Berosus festivus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
